# isProxy()

**Instance Method**

Returns a Boolean value that indicates whether the receiver does not descend from [doc://com.apple.objectivec/documentation/ObjectiveC/NSObject-swift.class].

## Declaration

```swift
func isProxy() -> Bool
```

## Return Value

[doc://com.apple.objectivec/documentation/ObjectiveC/NO] if the receiver really descends from [doc://com.apple.objectivec/documentation/ObjectiveC/NSObject-swift.class], otherwise [doc://com.apple.objectivec/documentation/ObjectiveC/YES].

## Discussion

This method is necessary because sending [doc://com.apple.objectivec/documentation/ObjectiveC/NSObjectProtocol/isKind(of:)] or [doc://com.apple.objectivec/documentation/ObjectiveC/NSObjectProtocol/isMember(of:)] to an [doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/Foundation/NSProxy] object will test the object the proxy stands in for, not the proxy itself. Use this method to test if the receiver is a proxy (or a member of some other root class).
